&gt; I want to make my Rectangle/Character move [...] but only once

Add a [`keyPressed()`](https://processing.org/reference/keyPressed_.html) event and call `move` from the event, but do not call it in [`draw()`](https://processing.org/reference/draw_.html).

Note `keyPressed` is called once every time a key is pressed. So the character moves only once, when a key is pressed. But since the operating systems may handle key repeats, the last pressed key ha to be stored. If the same key is pressed again before `keyReleased` occurs, it has to be skipped. e.g.:

```java
Character ch = new Character();
```

```java
int lastKey = 0;
void keyPressed() {
    if (lastKey != key) {
        lastKey = key; 
        ch.move();
    }
}

void keyReleased() {
    lastKey = 0;
}
```

In the example `ch` assumed to be your instance of `Character`.

